::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 116.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' ...You've found some interesting ingredients there. Now, take your pick.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 117.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Each drink has its own unique flavor, and the base ingredient sets the tone for the initial taste and the lingering aftertaste. So, {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|which one would you like to use as the base}}?
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 118.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Heh, you won't find a sweeter drink anywhere in Penacony, and that's what today's dream seekers crave.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 119.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Sweeter than Sousa Juice and more bitter than Dream Syrup. {{Rubi|"Dream in a Bottle"|Soulglad}} &mdash; that's a metaphor for Penacony itself.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 120.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The original formula is said to be Hanunue's favorite drink. It's sour and bitter, and the bubbles burst in your throat like swallowing rusty chains, evoking thoughts of dungeons and prisons.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 121.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Now that you've chosen the base, it's time to pick the adjunct &mdash; the ingredient that'll create a marvelous chemical reaction with the base. It should give an unforgettable taste without overpowering the main tone. So, {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|what's your choice for the adjunct}}?
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 122.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Bright Future... a taste that's been a long time coming.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 123.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' I'll never forget the flavor that danced on my tongue as Mikhail whisked me through the Dreamscape wilderness. Those were haunting times... too beautiful to be real.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 124.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The taste is... not very intense, yet evocative.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 125.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' After those despicables sent Mikhail away, I found myself lost in the wilderness of my dreams. They say that even the dirt here oozes with sweetness... Heh, all I tasted was stoic bitterness.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 126.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' This is the most pungent adjunct we have... and my personal favorite.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 127.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Before Mikhail left, the wrinkles at the corners of his eyes had deepened, like knife cuts. He mumbled, his breath too weak to climb up his throat, caught up in his chest. But I could smell it... the lingering scent of Penacony itself on that night.
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 104.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' Mikhail...?
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 128.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Almost there. Let's pick a decoration. Which style do you prefer? Anything you need, I've got it.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Straws with concentric circles.
:::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 129.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' {{Rubi|Concentric circles|The Harmony}}... May you always remember where you started.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Hanu's sign.
:::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 130.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' A {{Rubi|symbol|Hanunue}} of bravery and dauntlessness. May you break free from your shackles just like he did.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Coin-shaped lemon slices.
:::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 131.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The IPC's favorite... Ambitious, aren't you?
