===Listen to Gallagher's story{{subst:void|<!--103150120-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=trailblaze|location=The Reverie (Dreamscape)|update|Effortlessly, Gallagher presents you with an exquisite drink. Hopefully, the drink can keep your conversation with him from getting too boring.}}
{{Dialogue Start}}
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 157.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Alright, let's start with what we know based on the clues The Family has. It seems that Firefly isn't a local or an invited guest. In other words... she's a stowaway.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 158.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' She managed to fool me at first &mdash; my age must be getting the best of me. But here, on the Planet of Festivities, stowaways are a common sight. You're bound to run into one sooner or later. After the incident, the Hounds wasted no time searching for that girl in both the Dreamscape and reality.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 159.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' But here's the thing... We only received bad news, and the trickiest kind at that.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 160.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|She simply vanished}}, leaving no trace in the Dreamscape or reality, as if she had never come to Penacony at all.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 mar7th 134.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Huh? Does that mean...
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} "Death" eradicated her...
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 161.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' That's impossible. The problem now is not that '''she's dead''', but that it's as if '''she had never existed in the first place'''.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Maybe things will turn out different than what we think?
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 162.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Different...? Are you suggesting that girl wasn't actually killed? Come on, aren't you a witness in this case?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Is she a ghost!?
::{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 163.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Haha, a clever metaphor... Um, you were making a metaphor, right?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 164.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Let me be frank... This case, actually... is unlike anything the Bloodhound Family has dealt with before.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 108.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' "Dealt with before"? So... "Death" does happen in Penacony, if I understand correctly?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 165.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' You've witnessed it, so there's no need to hide. Even the shiniest city has its dark side. We're all adults here, surely I don't need to explain too much to you.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 166.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Confronting The Family based on that alone would be naive. Death may occur in sweet dreams &mdash; so what? Such events are highly unlikely and only affect a tiny number of people.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 167.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' If you really want to delve deeper into this case, you need to understand the true "problem" with The Family.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 109.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' I guess it's time to tell the story of that "Mikhail."
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 168.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' You're very perceptive. The Astral Express has received that music box, too, right? Do you know the secrets it holds?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 110.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' There's a message. "...Witness the impossible in the realm of dreams, find the Legacy of the Watchmaker, Father of Penacony, and thus the answer to the question: Why does life slumber?"
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 169.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' That's the exact wording.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 mar7th 135.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Hey, why are you laughing... Wait, did you write it? It's quite poetic.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 170.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' No... but I'm the officer in charge of this case, and how could I not know?... I'm sure you must have noticed that this message didn't come from The Family. You might even have guessed that the relationship between The Family and the Watchmaker isn't as close as it seems?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 111.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' That's just our speculation. Actually, it's hard to believe that the {{Rubi|Father of Penacony|The Watchmaker}} and its {{Rubi|actual managers|The Family}} are at odds.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 171.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Now I can assure you that your speculation is absolutely correct.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 172.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The Family has considered the Watchmaker as an enemy for a long time, but the Hounds haven't been able to track him down, as he seems to be living only in the characters and stories he created.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 173.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Let me ask you a question: Have you ever wondered why The Family allowed the Watchmaker to send out such a ridiculous message to the outside world, inviting you here and causing chaos?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 himeko 112.ogg}} '''Himeko:''' So, you want to seize this opportunity to expose the Watchmaker?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 174.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Well, now you understand why the Oak Family authorized the Nameless to assist in the investigation but kept you in the dark, right?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 175.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' ...Because the Watchmaker is not the legend of the Land of the Dreams at all. He's {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|the most shameful stain in the history of Penacony}}, and he's the root cause of all the anomalies in the Dreamscape.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} But what does this have to do with Mikhail?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 176.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' You don't get it? Well, I mean...
:{{tx}}
{{Dialogue End}}

===Head to the Clock Studios Theme Park{{subst:void|<!--103150124-->}}===
{{Mission Description|type=trailblaze|location=Clock Studios Theme Park|update|To better get his story across, Gallagher decides to make things fun by taking everyone to Clock Studios Theme Park. Using the facilities there as tools, he will give you all a lesson on the history of Penacony... Everyone understands that you are exhausted, but they hope you won't doze off.}}
{{Dialogue Start}}
:Some time later...
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 178.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' Here we are, Clock Studios Theme Park, the most popular entertainment center in Penacony.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 mar7th 136.ogg}} '''March 7th:''' Wait, aren't we supposed to be discussing "The Watchmaker"? I would have expected you to take us to maybe a library or an archive room of sorts, but an amusement park...?
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 179.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The culture of a city reflects its history in the most authentic way. To you, it's a fun place, but to me, it's a prison for the planet's past.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 180.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' You know that Penacony used to be the IPC's prison planet, right? All the prisoners were brought here, helping the Garden of Recollection salvage the leaking memoria from the Macro Void...
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 181.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' The prolonged exposure to high concentrations of memoria caused a unique phenomenon. The dreams of countless prisoners intersected and overlapped, and people started meeting each other in their dreams, living lives that were almost identical to reality.
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 182.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' But everything has a price, and sweet dreams are no exception. In the end, the dream world was unable to alleviate the suffering of prisoners in reality. One of the prisoners broke free from the IPC's shackles and fought for freedom...
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 183.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' ...He is {{Rubi|Hanu|Hanunue}}, the great leader of Dreamville, the great peacemaker, and the faithful companion of the underdogs.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} So, the character "Hanu" is based on a real-life person?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} So that Clockie cartoon is actually a documentary...
:{{A|VO chapter3 13 gallagher 184.ogg}} '''Gallagher:''' History is always written by the winners. However, it's undeniable that Clockie is an animation that draws from Penacony's actual history.
:{{tx}}
{{Dialogue End}}

